
[1]riddance

   RID'DANCE, n.

   1. Deliverance; a setting free; as riddance from all adversity.

   2. Disencumbrance.

   3. The act of clearing away.

   Thou shalt not make clean riddance of the corners of thy field. Lev.
   23.
